headline: Domino's Expands FFA Commitment with $100,000 in Scholarships for College Students Studying Agriculture Education
summary: Domino's Pizza Inc. (NYSE: DPZ) has funded scholarships for Future Farmers of America (FFA) students for seven years, and is excited to announce the strategic expansion of its scholarship program for the 2024-25 cycle. Domino's is funding 10 scholarships worth $10,000 each for FFA members working toward a college degree in agricultural education, with the intent to pursue a career as an agriculture science teacher.

headline: Warren Buffett Just Bought 4 Stocks. Here's the Best of the Bunch.
summary: Warren Buffett was a net seller of stocks for the eighth consecutive quarter in Q3.  Berkshire initiated new positions in only two stocks in the last quarter.  Its biggest addition was 1.28 million shares of pizza franchiser Domino's Pizza (NYSE: DPZ).
